d','','2459','','','2018-02-20 12:44:32','2018-02-20 12:44:32','',0,'http://www.shairab.com/?p=2459',11,'nav_menu_item','',0),(2460,1,'2017-12-14 04:31:06','2017-12-14 04:31:06',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','2460','','','2018-02-20 12:44:32','2018-02-20 12:44:32','',0,'http://www.shairab.com/?p=2460',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(2399,1,'2016-02-23 11:33:19','2016-02-23 11:33:19','','Blog','','publish','closed','closed','','blog','','','2016-02-23 11:33:19','2016-02-23 11:33:19','',0,'http://themes.muffingroup.com/be/lifestyle/?page_id=2399',0,'page','',0),(2461,1,'2017-12-14 04:31:06','2017-12-14 04:31:06',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','2461','','','2018-02-20 12:44:32','2018-02-20 12:44:32','',0,'http://www.shairab.com/?p=2461',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),(2494,1,'2016-02-26 14:13:44','2016-02-26 14:13:44','','home_lifestyle_blog_sectionbg1','','inherit','open','closed','','home_lifestyle_blog_sectionbg1','','','2016-02-26 14:13:44','2016-02-26 14:13:44','',2453,'http://www.shairab.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/home_lifestyle_blog_sectionbg1-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2277,1,'2014-05-08 09:29:42','2014-05-08 09:29:42','I woke up one day feeling completely burned out from work and decided that I needed to finally give myself time. I bought a ticket, packed my bags, hopped on a place, and experienced life away from work. I didnt have a concrete plan after my trip, I just knew I had to do this or it would have driven me nuts to sit behind my office desk again.\r\n\r\nI walked away.\r\n\r\nI walked away from a three year managerial job. Truth be told, being a manager at a young age is great, but it also takes a big toll on you. The highs, the lows, the pressures, the rewards, the camaraderie, the politics and everything else in between.\r\n\r\nAre you sure about this? Do you really want to quit your job and travel?\r\n\r\nThis was a question I had asked myself many times. I read all sorts of<a href=\"https://www.thrillist.com/travel/nation/why-you-should-not-quit-your-job-to-travel\">articles</a>that tell you not to do it. I get it, I understand that we live in a world where having a good job is a privilege. Sometimes it isnt a wise decision, but when I decided to travel, I wasnt thinking about all that. I just wanted what was best for me at that point in my life. For the many times I was selfless at work, it was time to be selfish.\r\n\r\nWhat did I learn?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><strong>Do not</strong><strong>bring your office</strong><strong>with you.</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nIm a bit of a workaholic. Sometimes I overdo it and unconsciously take it with me. I would bring the work home and do it there. When I used to travel, I would schedule cafe visits to finish work. I knew I had to take a real break this time. This trip was going to be about me, explore new experiences, revel in the new places, and simply enjoy.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Its okay not to have plans.</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nDont get me wrong, having a plan is great. Im a planner myself, but when circumstances force you to move on without a plan, it doesnt always mean you wont be fine. In fact, you can be more than fine. This is the time to take advantage and reflect. What do I really want to do in life? What do I really want? When your head is clear and your heart is still, something beautiful is bound to happen.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n 	<li><strong>You are allowed to spoil yourself when you travel.</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nEnjoy! Do something youve always wanted to do. You can book a five star hotel. You can eat any street food. You can buy that beautiful dress. You can go an extreme adventure. Theres nothing wrong with spoiling yourself but you have to know your limits. Just dont let anyone dictate what you should indulge on. You are allowed to spoil yourself while you are traveling, even if you just quit your job!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Learn as much as you c</strong><strong>an.</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nTraveling isnt just about the picture perfect things posted on Social Media. There are so much in between that doesnt make it to the online world and these are the most precious and insightful. Random conversations can provide daily learning and inspiration. Ask strangers for help and make instant friends. Some can be mean, some can be nice, but each and everyone teaches you something.You might even be able to learn about the business side of a place. If you feel like you can learn something beneficial for your professional growth then make the most out of it.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"5\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Self assessment happens A LOT when you are</strong><strong>on a trip (especially after quitting).</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nWhen you leave your job, it is normal to go through a phase of self assessment. Are you really ready? What can you do and what can you not do? When I traveled, I realized my many weaknesses, but I also discovered my strengths. Being in a different place allows you to meet people who will not sugarcoat things for you.This will trigger a lot of reflection with yourself. Trust me! When you know yourself better, you are able to move forward with a clearer mindset and a better version of yourself.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Giving myself a break after quitting my job</strong><strong>proved invaluable.</strong>Sometimes, you just need to breathe then once you exhale, you are ready to roll again for another show. While I was away, I received a job offer I couldnt say no to which is why I came back. This time, nature is my office. I guess not having a plan is the plan after all.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2508\" src=\"http://www.shairab.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Movenpick.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"720\" />','I Burned Out and Traveled, Heres What I Learned','Quisque justo augue ut urna eu eros. Sed id elit tincidunt et, fermentum vel, wisi. In vitae erat eget arcu nunc venenatis placerat, molestie tristique commodo. Cras turpis vitae ante. Praesent magna ac nunc. Vivamus volutpat.','publish','open','open','','i-burned-out-and-traveled-heres-what-i-learned','','','2017-12-14 05:06:56','2017-12-14 05:06:56','',0,'http://themes.muffingroup.com/betheme/?p=2277',0,'post','',0),(2279,1,'2014-05-07 09:30:33','2014-05-07 09:30:33','<div class=\"et_post_meta_wrapper\">When the Pyramid first opened its doors to the public, the hype was intense. Everyone took photos at almost every corner of this undeniably unique and lovely structure. The name itself makes you curious enough to jump out of your seat and head over to IT Park. Since I live and work in the island of Mactan, it took me quite some time to visit. When I finally had the chance, I was greeted by the beaming lights which made it worth my long drive.</div>\r\n<div class=\"entry-content\">\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Here are the things I absolutely love about the Pyramid:</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-27748\" src=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-exterior.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1242px) 100vw, 1242px\" srcset=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-exterior.jpg 1242w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-exterior-306x300.jpg 306w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-exterior-768x753.jpg 768w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-exterior-386x379.jpg 386w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-exterior-610x598.jpg 610w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-exterior-1080x1059.jpg 1080w\" alt=\"6 Things I Love About The Pyramid - Zerothreetwo - Shaira Berame\" width=\"1242\" height=\"1218\" />\r\n<h2>1. It is literally a PYRAMID.</h2>\r\nTheres no building in the city or maybe even in the whole province that possesses such a shape. Of course, it is meant to remind us of the pyramids in Egypt. Pyramids remain to be a fascination to many including me. Why? If you dig deeper to a pyramids meaning, you will find<a href=\"http://www.deccanchronicle.com/lifestyle/viral-and-trending/030316/pyramid-healing-power-which-heal-seven-chakras-of-body.html\">various interesting beliefs</a>about why the shape is special. It is believed that a pyramid has supernatural or paranormal properties  preservation of food, strengthening of wellbeing, etc. Trivia  the collective theories regarding the benefits of pyramids are called Pyramidology. In this case, I can guarantee that this Pyramid has the power of wine and cheese!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-27750\" src=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-instagrammable-spot.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1242px) 100vw, 1242px\" srcset=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-instagrammable-spot.jpg 1242w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-instagrammable-spot-382x270.jpg 382w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-instagrammable-spot-768x544.jpg 768w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-instagrammable-spot-536x379.jpg 536w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-instagrammable-spot-610x432.jpg 610w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-instagrammable-spot-400x284.jpg 400w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-instagrammable-spot-1080x764.jpg 1080w\" alt=\"6 Things I Love About The Pyramid - Zerothreetwo - Shaira Berame\" width=\"1242\" height=\"879\" />\r\n<h2>2. Every spot is INSTAGRAM worthy</h2>\r\nWith the rise of Social Media use, particularly Instagram, many people not only visit for good food, but also good ambiance. In fact, people always ask me for restaurant recommendations with instagram worthy spots. This is how you know you are talking to true blue millennial! Pyramid is the new perfect place to take those OOTD or OOTN shots while waiting for your orders.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-27751\" src=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Pizza-and-macaroons.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1242px) 100vw, 1242px\" srcset=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Pizza-and-macaroons.jpg 1242w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Pizza-and-macaroons-300x300.jpg 300w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Pizza-and-macaroons-768x769.jpg 768w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Pizza-and-macaroons-378x379.jpg 378w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Pizza-and-macaroons-610x611.jpg 610w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Pizza-and-macaroons-1080x1082.jpg 1080w\" alt=\"6 Things I Love About The Pyramid - Zerothreetwo - Shaira Berame\" width=\"1242\" height=\"1244\" />\r\n<h2>3. The best FRENCH MACARONS in Cebu</h2>\r\nI have tried so many French macarons in Cebu. Unfortunately, theres very few that are good. For now, the best ones are found in the Pyramid. Can you guess which ones are my favourite? The photo says it all!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-27752\" src=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Sisig-FB-page.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" srcset=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Sisig-FB-page.jpg 960w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Sisig-FB-page-301x300.jpg 301w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Sisig-FB-page-768x766.jpg 768w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Sisig-FB-page-380x379.jpg 380w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Sisig-FB-page-610x609.jpg 610w\" alt=\"6 Things I Love About The Pyramid - Zerothreetwo - Shaira Berame\" width=\"960\" height=\"958\" />\r\n<h2>4. This is where class and casual blend well</h2>\r\nWith its French macarons, wine and cheese, Pyramid has an air of sophistication. Most people are intimidated and think that the prices are not affordable. Its funny because every time I take friends there for the first time, they are surprised by how affordable the food choices are. Its a very classy place but its just also really casual. You can dress nicely but you can just also dress down but while enjoying wine and cheese with friends.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-27753 size-full\" src=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/pyramid-plan.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2400px) 100vw, 2400px\" srcset=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/pyramid-plan.jpg 2400w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/pyramid-plan-382x158.jpg 382w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/pyramid-plan-768x318.jpg 768w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/pyramid-plan-569x236.jpg 569w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/pyramid-plan-610x253.jpg 610w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/pyramid-plan-1080x447.jpg 1080w\" alt=\"6 Things I Love About The Pyramid - Zerothreetwo - Shaira Berame\" width=\"2400\" height=\"994\" />\r\n<h2>5. It doesnt hurt your budget!</h2>\r\nAside from good food, good ambiance, the most crucial factor people consider when choosing a place to go to is the price. Although many people would really pay for expensive good food, it is easier to make people come back if it doesnt hurt their budget. Pyramid offers very affordable food and drink choices so I dont wonder why people keep coming back.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-27754\" src=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-wine-and-cheese.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1242px) 100vw, 1242px\" srcset=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-wine-and-cheese.jpg 1242w, http://zerothreetwo.