none size-full wp-image-27748\" src=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-exterior.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1242px) 100vw, 1242px\" srcset=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-exterior.jpg 1242w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-exterior-306x300.jpg 306w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-exterior-768x753.jpg 768w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-exterior-386x379.jpg 386w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-exterior-610x598.jpg 610w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-exterior-1080x1059.jpg 1080w\" alt=\"6 Things I Love About The Pyramid - Zerothreetwo - Shaira Berame\" width=\"1242\" height=\"1218\" />\r\n<h2>1. It is literally a PYRAMID.</h2>\r\nTheres no building in the city or maybe even in the whole province that possesses such a shape. Of course, it is meant to remind us of the pyramids in Egypt. Pyramids remain to be a fascination to many including me. Why? If you dig deeper to a pyramids meaning, you will find<a href=\"http://www.deccanchronicle.com/lifestyle/viral-and-trending/030316/pyramid-healing-power-which-heal-seven-chakras-of-body.html\">various interesting beliefs</a>about why the shape is special. It is believed that a pyramid has supernatural or paranormal properties  preservation of food, strengthening of wellbeing, etc. Trivia  the collective theories regarding the benefits of pyramids are called Pyramidology. In this case, I can guarantee that this Pyramid has the power of wine and cheese!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-27750\" src=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-instagrammable-spot.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1242px) 100vw, 1242px\" srcset=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-instagrammable-spot.jpg 1242w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-instagrammable-spot-382x270.jpg 382w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-instagrammable-spot-768x544.jpg 768w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-instagrammable-spot-536x379.jpg 536w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-instagrammable-spot-610x432.jpg 610w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-instagrammable-spot-400x284.jpg 400w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-instagrammable-spot-1080x764.jpg 1080w\" alt=\"6 Things I Love About The Pyramid - Zerothreetwo - Shaira Berame\" width=\"1242\" height=\"879\" />\r\n<h2>2. Every spot is INSTAGRAM worthy</h2>\r\nWith the rise of Social Media use, particularly Instagram, many people not only visit for good food, but also good ambiance. In fact, people always ask me for restaurant recommendations with instagram worthy spots. This is how you know you are talking to true blue millennial! Pyramid is the new perfect place to take those OOTD or OOTN shots while waiting for your orders.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-27751\" src=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Pizza-and-macaroons.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1242px) 100vw, 1242px\" srcset=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Pizza-and-macaroons.jpg 1242w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Pizza-and-macaroons-300x300.jpg 300w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Pizza-and-macaroons-768x769.jpg 768w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Pizza-and-macaroons-378x379.jpg 378w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Pizza-and-macaroons-610x611.jpg 610w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Pizza-and-macaroons-1080x1082.jpg 1080w\" alt=\"6 Things I Love About The Pyramid - Zerothreetwo - Shaira Berame\" width=\"1242\" height=\"1244\" />\r\n<h2>3. The best FRENCH MACARONS in Cebu</h2>\r\nI have tried so many French macarons in Cebu. Unfortunately, theres very few that are good. For now, the best ones are found in the Pyramid. Can you guess which ones are my favourite? The photo says it all!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-27752\" src=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Sisig-FB-page.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" srcset=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Sisig-FB-page.jpg 960w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Sisig-FB-page-301x300.jpg 301w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Sisig-FB-page-768x766.jpg 768w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Sisig-FB-page-380x379.jpg 380w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-Sisig-FB-page-610x609.jpg 610w\" alt=\"6 Things I Love About The Pyramid - Zerothreetwo - Shaira Berame\" width=\"960\" height=\"958\" />\r\n<h2>4. This is where class and casual blend well</h2>\r\nWith its French macarons, wine and cheese, Pyramid has an air of sophistication. Most people are intimidated and think that the prices are not affordable. Its funny because every time I take friends there for the first time, they are surprised by how affordable the food choices are. Its a very classy place but its just also really casual. You can dress nicely but you can just also dress down but while enjoying wine and cheese with friends.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-27753 size-full\" src=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/pyramid-plan.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2400px) 100vw, 2400px\" srcset=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/pyramid-plan.jpg 2400w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/pyramid-plan-382x158.jpg 382w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/pyramid-plan-768x318.jpg 768w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/pyramid-plan-569x236.jpg 569w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/pyramid-plan-610x253.jpg 610w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/pyramid-plan-1080x447.jpg 1080w\" alt=\"6 Things I Love About The Pyramid - Zerothreetwo - Shaira Berame\" width=\"2400\" height=\"994\" />\r\n<h2>5. It doesnt hurt your budget!</h2>\r\nAside from good food, good ambiance, the most crucial factor people consider when choosing a place to go to is the price. Although many people would really pay for expensive good food, it is easier to make people come back if it doesnt hurt their budget. Pyramid offers very affordable food and drink choices so I dont wonder why people keep coming back.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-27754\" src=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-wine-and-cheese.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1242px) 100vw, 1242px\" srcset=\"http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-wine-and-cheese.jpg 1242w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-wine-and-cheese-302x300.jpg 302w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-wine-and-cheese-768x763.jpg 768w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-wine-and-cheese-381x379.jpg 381w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-wine-and-cheese-610x606.jpg 610w, http://zerothreetwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pyramid-wine-and-cheese-1080x1073.jpg 1080w\" alt=\"6 Things I Love About The Pyramid - Zerothreetwo - Shaira Berame\" width=\"1242\" height=\"1234\" />\r\n<h2>6. The Wine and Cheese pairing is magical</h2>\r\nNo words for this! You have to try it yourself.\r\n\r\n</div>','6 Favorite Filipino Desserts and Where to Find it in Cebu','Bibendum tellus, fringilla ut, eleifend pede id nulla ac ligula at neque. Vestibulum ante sodales neque ut quam placerat id, orci. Integer aliquam. Etiam tempor varius, quam elit justo ac accumsan id, eleifend lectus non.','publish','open','open','','6-favorite-filipino-desserts-and-where-to-find-it-in-cebu','','','2017-12-15 03:31:01','2017-12-15 03:31:01','',0,'http://themes.muffingroup.com/betheme/?p=2281',0,'post','',0),(2283,1,'2014-05-05 09:34:27','2014-05-05 09:34:27','One of the things I sometimes wish I have is a First World Passport. Dont get me wrong  Im a proud Filipino but lets be honest, traveling would be so much easier if we didnt need a visa to our dream destinations. For many Filipinos, these dream destinations require a VISA! Reality hurts  A LOT!\r\n\r\nThe struggle of getting a visa scares and intimidates many thus, it delays a lot of travel plans. As the only one among my sisters left with a Philippine passport, I made sure this will not discourage me. In fact, I find visa application process now super fun. One of the most sought after visa (if not the most) is the<a href=\"http://www.schengenvisainfo.com/schengen-visa-countries-list/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-wpel-link=\"external\">Schengen visa</a>which allows you to travel to 26 countries in Europe.\r\n\r\nOn my<a href=\"https://twomonkeystravelgroup.com/explore-gothenburg-sweden/#comments\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">previous post</a>, I talked about Gothenburg. Before I enjoyed the place, I went through the challenge of getting a Schengen visa. Heres the thing  I obtained a 3-month visa to Europe although it was good for one entry only (as it was what I really requested for). To be granted a 3-month visa as a tourist is not that common especially if you are applying to a Scandinavian country as they have very high standards of living. If you are planning to apply for a Schengen visa, these are the simple tips that I can give you based on my personal experiences.\r\n<h2><strong>1. DO YOUR HOMEWORK</strong></h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-41615 aligncenter\" src=\"https://twomonkeystravelgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/5-Simple-Tips-to-Follow-When-You-Apply-For-a-Schengen-Visa.png\" alt=\"5 Simple Tips to Follow When You Apply For a Schengen Visa\" width=\"702\" height=\"454\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAs clich as it may sound, the most important thing before applying for any visa is<u>to do some research but DO NOT over do it</u>, or you will go crazy! In my case, Sweden was my main destination, so I applied for my Schengen visa from the said countrys embassy. Obviously, my research was focused on Swedens requirements, but I did check with other countries requirements for comparison. Cebu has a Visa Center so I was able to lodge my application and requirements there which were then forwarded to the Manila office for review and approval. Some will no longer require an interview especially if you have all the needed requirements but because I was requesting for a long period of stay (90 days!), I was called for an interview in Manila. Research the requirements of the country where you want to enter and arrive then take it from there.\r\n<h2><strong>2. STUDY YOUR HOMEWORK</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-8505\" src=\"https://twomonkeystravelgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Plotting-your-leaves-early-means-more-time-for-travel-planning.jpg\" alt=\"Learnings from a Corporate Travel Junkie\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" />\r\n\r\nOnce the research part is over, dont just go through it  read it!<u>Read it not once or twice but thrice or even more</u>. It pays to know the details of what is being asked of you. Many of us practice the okay na yan (Its okay, or that should be okay) Well, if you want to be 101% sure that you will be granted a visa then carefully go through and review your requirements. Make sure you are familiar with it so in case you will be asked about it randomly, you will know what to answer. I had a friend who was invited by her boyfriend to visit Spain, and when she was called for an interview, questions regarding her boyfriends job, salary, etc. were thrown at her, and because she was not able to orient herself on the specific details, she got tensed and failed to answer properly. Visa denied. Dont be like this!\r\n\r\nIf its your boyfriend who is inviting you, its not enough that you just know hes an engineer. You have to know the details about the job and other vital information of the person inviting you. My sister was the one who invited me, so I made sure I know exactly what her job title is, what the company does, how much she earns, what her schedule is like, etc. Since she is an accountant (Finance Manager) which is not a very common position filled by Filipinos there (especially because Sweden is very particular with the mastery of their language), I was stillasked about her job history and academic background. Luckily, I came prepared enough to answer all these. It was like one question after another, so you have to keep a sharp mind when answering the questions. They record and take note of the answers so you can never lie. Just dont.\r\n<h2><strong>3. REVIEW AND REVISE AS NEEDED\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<div id=\"attachment_41602\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-41602 size-large\" src=\"https://twomonkeystravelgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/5-Simple-Tips-to-Follow-When-You-Apply-For-a-Schengen-Visa-800x479.jpg\" alt=\"5 Simple Tips to Follow When You Apply For a Schengen Visa\" width=\"800\" height=\"479\" />\r\n<p class=\"wp-caption-text\">PHOTO BY<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/markhillary/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-wpel-link=\"external\">MARK HILLARY</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nSo aside from settling with an OK quality of documents, one of the things that will surely deny you of your visa is your refusal or laziness to revise something when you know its needed. How many of us are guilty with this? We dont like to revise or repeat something because its a hassle. One of the things I had to revise was my<a href=\"http://www.worldnomads.com/Turnstile/AffiliateLink?partnerCode=2monk&amp;source=&amp;utm_source=2monk&amp;utm_content=link&amp;path=https://www.worldnomads.com/travel-insurance\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-wpel-link=\"external\">travel insurance</a>dates. They look very closely to this so be sure you have the correct dates and ideally, you should give some allowance.\r\n<h2><strong>4. CONFIDENCE IS KEY</strong></h2>\r\n<h2><strong><img class=\"size-full wp-image-12212 aligncenter\" src=\"https://twomonkeystravelgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Schengen.jpg\" alt=\"Planning to travel to Europe? How to Apply for Schengen Visa\" width=\"800\" height=\"469\" /></strong></h2>\r\nAs mentioned, if you only plan to go for a two-week tour and your documents are already strong then there is a big chance, you will no longer be called for an interview, and your visa will just be granted directly. Sometimes you will be called for an interview. This doesnt really mean that you have lesser chances of getting a visa, but this can mean that they need to verify some things regarding your application.\r\n\r\nIf you are called for an interview, remember that in any interview whether it be for a job, a visa, Confidence is key. Well, its easier said than done but if you have followed tips 1-3 then the interview should be a piece of cake for you.<u>Two rules: Be honest and do your best to express your thoughts clearly.</u>With my experience, I was interviewed by none other than the Deputy Head of the Visa Section. Lucky me!! Before I was called in, I had a short talk (chika moment) with the security guard. He asked me what country I was applying for and I replied Sweden. He then said Mam, ang daming umiiyak dito kasi na deny (Mam, many cry here because their visa application was denied!). Wow manong guard, you are very encouraging!\r\n<h2><strong>5. THINK OF YOUR VISA APPLICATION AS FINAL EXAM IN UNIVERSITY THAT YOU HAVE TO PASS ( WITH FLYING COLORS)</strong><strong>\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-31492 aligncenter\" src=\"https://twomonkeystravelgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Visa-Experiences-Around-the-World-Trip-Filipina-Backpacker-in-Bahamas-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Visa Experiences Around the World Trip - Filipina Backpacker in Bahamas\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" /></strong></h2>\r\nObtaining a Schengen Visa is not as complicated as what most people think. Its actually an easy process. Like your final exam in University that you must pass, it requires hard work and patience plus a sprinkle of luck coupled with a lot of prayers. Think that rejection is not an option. Do not settle with so-so requirements. Do not settle with so-so answers and most of all, do not settle with a MAYBE approved  always push and aim for DEFINITELY approved.\r\n\r\nAlways aim high if you want to fly high!','5 SIMPLE TIPS TO FOLLOW WHEN YOU APPLY FOR A SCHENGEN VISA','Cum sociis natoque penatibus et malesuada sit amet quam. Aliquam nonummy, tellus ante mollis sodales. Quisque nulla. Suspendisse vitae ante. Donec sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit. Sed dignissim vitae, vulputate imperdiet.','publish','open','open','','5-simple-tips-to-follow-when-you-apply-for-a-schengen-visa','','','2017-12-15 03:45:52','2017-12-15 03:45:52','',0,'http://themes.muffingroup.com/betheme/?p=2283',0,'post','',0),(2437,1,'2016-02-24 15:52:47','2016-02-24 15:52:47','<div class=\"column one-second\">[text* your-name placeholder \"Your name\"] </div>\n<div class=\"column one-second\">[email* your-email placeholder \"Your e-mail\"] </div>\n<div class=\"column one\">[text your-subject placeholder \"Subject\"] </div>\n<div class=\"column one\">[textarea your-message x6 placeholder \"Message\"]</div>\n<div class=\"column one\">[submit \"Send a message\"]</div>\nBeLifestyle - BeTheme \"[your-subject]\"\n[your-name] <wordpress@themes.muffingroup.com>\nFrom: [your-name] <[your-email]>\nSubject: [your-subject]\n\nMessage Body:\n[your-message]\n\n--\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on BeLifestyle - BeTheme (http://themes.muffingroup.com/be/lifestyle)\nnoreply@gmail.com\nReply-To: [your-email]\n\n\n\n\nBeLifestyle - BeTheme \"[y